reviewText:
I am utterly impressed. At first, I could not believe another shoot-them-all game would change my view on the genre. So, feeling quite sceptically, I purchased it and prepared for another meaningless mix of violence and cursing.

Well, there was a lot of violence and cursing indeed. However, it was flavoured with a great concept of a single man creating his own world. His own war. His own enemies. And, after all, sacrificing his people for the sake of his own illusions.

Frankly, I find the Spec Ops relatively close to the Bioshock Infinite. It is far more than shooting. Both games are about seeking the truth and realising that there is no truth. There is reality. Or plenty (in case of Bioshock).

But let me get back to the matter of this particular game. Amongst all shooters that I have played, this one I doubtlessly call the #1. That I do for that the game possesses all of the following:
1. Great storyline;
2. High-quality graphics;
3. Distinctive characters;
4. Lots of shooting;
5. Handy gameplay;
6. Right of choice;
7. Unexpected ending.

What do I have to say for conclusion? I certainly recommend this game to everyone who values both engaging story and exciting action. A must-play!
